    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-05-20T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-05-20T15:00:00-05:00" n="195"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d195">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.00/759: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Muccio</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-20T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 20, 1936—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:13 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>26. Toro scheduled to enter La Paz 5 p.m., with grand display of force. No
                    announcement of the composition of his Junta whether purely military or
                    mixed.</p>
                <p>La Paz superficially tranquil. Situation continues delicate and unpredictable.
                    Labor element believed to consider themselves thwarted in their aspirations.
                    Labor Federation still ensconced in Municipal Building. Rumors of lack of army
                    solidarity continue. Repeated to Buenos Aires.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Muccio</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
